# Realtime Server

Handles:

* player connections
* room management
* game state updates
* broadcasting events

```
Realtime Server

 ├ Connection Manager
 ├ Room Manager
 ├ Player State
 ├ Game Loop
 └ Event Broadcast
```

Example server structure:

```
server
 ├ realtime
 │
 │  ├ rooms
 │  │   gameRoom.ts
 │
 │  ├ entities
 │  │   player.ts
 │
 │  ├ systems
 │  │   movement.ts
 │  │   physics.ts
 │
 │  └ sync
 │      stateSync.ts
 │
 └ index.ts
```

---

# Game State Synchronization

Recommended model:

```
Server Authoritative
```

Flow:

```
client -> send input
server -> simulate world
server -> broadcast updated state
```

Example message flow:

```
client
  move_forward

server
  update position

server
  broadcast new position
```

Advantages:

* cheat prevention
* consistent world state
* easier debugging

---

# Networking Protocol Example

Client → Server

```
{
  type: "MOVE",
  direction: "forward",
  timestamp: 123456
}
```

Server → Client

```
{
  type: "STATE_UPDATE",
  players: [...]
}
```

